GREER, SC-- Dustin Dewayne Anders, 21, of 124 Skyland Circle, died August 24, 2007.
A native of Greenville County, son of Dale Dey Wicker and Shirley Ann Stafford Dewayne, he was self-employed as an independent operator for Emcon Technologies. He was of the methodological faith, enjoyed riding dirt bikes, enjoyed being outdoors and was an avid Green Bay Packers fan.
Surviving are his wife, Jessica Lunsford Anders who he married January 5, 2007; his mother, Kathy Neeley Widmon of Puerto Banus in Spain, brothers and sisters-in-law, Bryce and Emily Tinnin of Atlanta, Joshua and Julian Tinnin of Pisgah Forest and Harley and Janelle Tinnin and nephew Alexander Thomas of the home; maternal grandparents, Fred and Mary Wicker of Taylors, SC and paternal grandparents, Ralph Paris and Pauline Brown Paris of Greenville;

